CAPE TOWN - A Durbanville mom, her two children and their domestic worker are recovering after surviving a nightmarish robbery in which four suspects entered their home and demanded money from the safe.Police said that last Thursday the family was at home in Bukkettraube Street, Shiraz Villas, Oude Westhof, when four men entered through the main door.The mom was in a room and the domestic worker was in the kitchen when the suspects went upstairs and pointed a gun at the mom.“One of the suspects wanted to know where the money was. Before she could answer they took her to the main bedroom. They told her that they would kill her child if she didn’t tell them where the money was.“They strangled the complainant (mom) and helper and took the safe that was in the stockroom. The safe contained R35 800.“The suspects fled the scene by jumping over the fence.“A house robbery case will be investigated by the Durbanville police.”Anyone with information can anonymously call CrimeStop on 08600 10111 or SMS Crime Line on 32211.Meanwhile, in Somerset West on that same day, seven suspects involved in a business robbery were arrested.According to the complainant, she was at the store assisting a customer when she heard her colleague screaming.Wanting to assist she noticed an unknown man armed with a firearm in the store.The suspect threatened her and he was accompanied by another armed suspect.“The suspects took her and two of her colleagues to the control room where they demanded that she open the room. Inside the suspects took a large sum of cash and several cellphones.“Later at about .:30pm police in Khayelitsha spotted the getaway vehicle with one suspect inside.“A chase ensued and the suspect ran into a house in Samora Machel Street.“Police followed and inside the house the suspect and six others were arrested. The stolen property and some of the cash were recovered.”Cape Times